<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib">147. Goldwater, Robert, and Marco Treves, eds. Artists on Art: From the XIVto the XX Century. New York: Pantheon, 1972. 500 pp. Index, B/W illus. ISBN 0-394~70900-4. </p><p class="annot">This is a compilation of excerpts of writings by many artists --including Alberti, Vasari, Palomino, Bossi, Delacroix, Corot, Seurat, Signac, Van Gogh -- whose statements touch on various aspects of color theory and application. This publication offers a convenient starting point for the reader interested in the thoughts of practitioners. </p></div>
